		<Placemark id="0A0F0C4E863F2B2D7214">
			<name>Yinchuan/ &quot;Tangut&quot;</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<bettercanvas-portal style="overflow: visible; position: relative; width: 0px; height: 0px; display: block;"></bettercanvas-portal><div>The Realm of George, descendant of 'Prester John' and title holder of the same. (Polo and Latham, <i>The Travels of Marco Polo</i>. 106.)<br></div><div><br></div><div>Link legend of prester john and cultural, historical implications here.<br></div><div><br></div><div><a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/community.14776185">https://www.jstor.org/stable/community.14776185</a>&nbsp; Relevant Image<br></div><div><br></div><div class="csl-bib-body" style="line-height: 1.35; margin-left: 2em; text-indent: -2em;"><div class="csl-entry" style="margin-bottom: 1em;">ANONYMOUS / ITALY (FLORENCE) (XV century), artist. <i>Map. So-Called Genoese Planisphere. Africa: Representation of Black Rulers and of Prester John (at the Eastern Point).</i> n.d. Accessed May 10, 2026. <a href="https://jstor.org/stable/community.14776185">https://jstor.org/stable/community.14776185</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry" style="margin-bottom: 1em;">Helleiner, Karl F. “Prester John’s Letter: A Mediaeval Utopia.” <i>Phoenix</i> 13, no. 2 (1959): 47. <a href="https://doi.org/10.2307/1086970">https://doi.org/10.2307/1086970</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry" style="margin-bottom: 1em;">Heng, Geraldine. “Sex, Lies, and Paradise: The Assassins, Prester John, and the Fabulation of Civilizational Identities.” <i>Differences</i> 23, no. 1 (2012): 1–31. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1215/10407391-1533511">https://doi.org/10.1215/10407391-1533511</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry" style="margin-bottom: 1em;">Kurt, Andrew. “The Search for Prester John, a Projected Crusade and the Eroding Prestige of Ethiopian Kings, <i>c</i> .1200– <i>c</i> .1540.” <i>Journal of Medieval History</i> 39, no. 3 (2013): 297–320. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/03044181.2013.789978">https://doi.org/10.1080/03044181.2013.789978</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry">Valtrová, Jana. “Beyond the Horizons of Legends: Traditional Imagery and Direct Experience in Medieval Accounts of Asia.” <i>Numen</i> 57, no. 2 (2010): 154–85. <a href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/27793840">http://www.jstor.org/stable/27793840</a>.<br></div></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
