		<Placemark id="03991D52443F24D7494E">
			<name>Kashgar</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<bettercanvas-portal style="overflow: visible; position: relative; width: 0px; height: 0px; display: block;"></bettercanvas-portal><div><span style="overflow: visible; position: relative; width: 0px; height: 0px; display: block;"></span><br></div><div>Descent from the Pamir mountains: link Yam network explanation here due to its strategic position on the network, both spatially and geographically (Polo and Latham, <i>The Travels of Marco Polo</i>, 150.)<br></div><div><br></div><div class="csl-bib-body" style="line-height: 1.35; margin-left: 2em; text-indent: -2em;"><br></div><div class="csl-bib-body" style="line-height: 1.35; margin-left: 2em; text-indent: -2em;"><div class="csl-entry">Золотоордынское обозрение. “2023, Vol. 11, No. 1. Meriç S., Paşaoğlu D.D.,” March 27, 2023. <a href="http://goldhorde.ru/en/stati2023-1-3/">http://goldhorde.ru/en/stati2023-1-3/</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry">Eği̇lmez, Savaş, and Gönül Bayram Kalkan. “Yam (Post/Communication) Organization in Mongols.” <i>Turcology Research (Online)</i> 1, no. 77 (2023). doi:<a href="https://doi.org/10.5152/jtri.2023.23196">10.5152/jtri.2023.23196</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry">Shim, Hosung. “The Postal Roads of the Great Khans in Central Asia under the Mongol-Yuan Empire.” <i>Journal of Song-Yuan Studies</i> 44, no. 1 (2014): 405–69. doi:<a href="https://doi.org/10.1353/sys.2014.0006">10.1353/sys.2014.0006</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry">Williamson, Alayna. “Technological Developments in the Mongol Empire.” <i>Science Technology and Society a Student Led Exploration</i>, July 29, 2020. <a href="https://opentextbooks.clemson.edu/sciencetechnologyandsociety/chapter/technological-developments-in-the-mongol-empire/">https://opentextbooks.clemson.edu/sciencetechnologyandsociety/chapter/technological-developments-in-the-mongol-empire/</a>.<br></div></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
