		<Placemark id="0FBA2D8A163F2F347BEC">
			<name>Sar-e Sang</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<bettercanvas-portal style="overflow: visible; position: relative; width: 0px; height: 0px; display: block;"></bettercanvas-portal><div>The location of Sar-e Sang mine, a Lapis Lazuli exploitation source, and one that held a practical monopoly over the world supply for most of the historical record, since antiquity. Not visited, but just upstream from a stop of the route and noted for its extant lapis trade(Marco Polo and R. E. Latham, <i>The Travels of Marco Polo</i>, Repr, Penguin Classics (Harmondsworth [etc.]: Penguin, 1978), 76.)<br></div><div><br></div><div class="csl-bib-body" style="line-height: 1.35; margin-left: 2em; text-indent: -2em;"><div class="csl-entry">Guidorzi, Laura, Marta Magalini, Alessandro Re, Alessandro Borghi, Massimo Vidale, Leonardo La Torre, Valentino Rigato, et al. “Provenance Attribution of Lapis Lazuli Rocks Processed at the Bronze Age Archaeological Site of Shahr-i Sokhta (Iran).” <i>Journal of Archaeological Science: Reports</i> 67 (November 2025): 105411. doi:<a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jasrep.2025.105411">10.1016/j.jasrep.2025.105411</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry">Khamidov, Odiljon. “The Role of Lapis Lazuli in Central Asia in the Period of the Bronze Age.” <i>“O‘Zbekiston Milliy Universitetining Ilm-Fan Rivoji va Jamiyat Taraqqiyotida Tutgan o‘Rni” Mavzusidagi Xalqaro Ilmiy-Amaliy Konferensiyasi Ma’Ruzalari to‘plami (II Qism)</i>, January 1, 2023. <a href="https://www.academia.edu/102466298/The_Role_of_Lapis_Lazuli_in_Central_Asia_in_the_period_of_the_Bronze_Age">https://www.academia.edu/102466298/The_Role_of_Lapis_Lazuli_in_Central_Asia_in_the_period_of_the_Bronze_Age</a>.<br></div><div class="csl-entry">Polo, Marco, and R. E. Latham. <i>The Travels of Marco Polo</i>. Repr. Penguin Classics. Harmondsworth [etc.]: Penguin, 1978.<br></div><div class="csl-entry">Rezaye, Fatima, James Darling, and Aqashireen Zamani. “Afghanistan’s Mineral Resources: A Historical Review of Geological Studies and Discoveries.” <i>International Geology Review</i>, April 15, 2026, 1–16. doi:<a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/00206814.2026.2655387">10.1080/00206814.2026.2655387</a>.<br></div></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>]]></description>
