	<Folder id="0D6E4BEB923F4405AF98">
		<name>(1291-1293) The return West/ Escorting princess Kokachin</name>
		<open>1</open>
		<description><![CDATA[<bettercanvas-portal style="overflow: visible; position: relative; width: 0px; height: 0px; display: block;"></bettercanvas-portal><div><span style="overflow: visible; position: relative; width: 0px; height: 0px; display: block;"></span>This is the sea route that Marco Polo and his diplomatic party would have made when allowed to return west. The purpose of the journey was to escort a princess to Iran; however, at this point, Southeast Asia, India, and the Arabian Sea would be described.<br></div><div><br></div><div>(Chapters 6-9)<br></div>]]></description>
		<styleUrl>#__managed_style_1D7FDEF4043F6294FB3F</styleUrl>
