		<Placemark id="0837623F983F25B293C0">
			<name>Santhome Cathedral Basilica</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<bettercanvas-portal style="overflow: visible; position: relative; width: 0px; height: 0px; display: block;"></bettercanvas-portal><div><span style="overflow: visible; position: relative; width: 0px; height: 0px; display: block;"></span><br></div><div>The burial place of St. Thomas the Apostle, which Polo notes. This is a place where Polo anchors his understanding of a distant location by a Christian worldview. (Marco Polo and R. E. Latham, <i>The Travels of Marco Polo</i>, Repr, Penguin Classics (Harmondsworth [etc.]: Penguin, 1978), 365.)<br></div>]]></description>
			<LookAt>
